    <h1>CourseSmart Requirements</h1>

    <hr />
    <h2>General</h2>

    <p>CourseSmart provides support for a single course with a small to moderate number of
      students. If multiple courses need to be supported, multiple instances of the
      CourseSmart server need to be run.</p>

    <p>CourseSmart provides the following features:</p>

    <ul>

      <li>
        <p>The instructor can provide course information in "units" consisting of some
          course materials, an optional assignment, and an optional quiz.</p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>Students can submit their assignments to the system where they are timestamped
          and stored until the instructor or grader downloads them for grading. Students
          can take quizzes on-line in a time frame specified by the instructor.</p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>The instructor can create one or more discussion boards and students can post
          messages to these boards.</p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>Students can view their grades using the system. The result of an on-line quiz
          is automatically entered into the grade book.</p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>The instructor can define a glossary of term/definition pairs that the
          CourseSmart server automatically injects into certain documents.</p>
      </li>

    </ul>

    <p>In addition CourseSmart provides a well defined protocol between the client and the
      server, opening up the possibility of independent, specialized implementations of
      either component.</p>

    <p>Users can have one of three predefined roles: Instructors, Graders, and Students. A
      user is allowed to have multiple roles. An Instructor user is predefined, but
      additional users can be assigned the instructor role. It is also allowed to have
      multiple users with the grader role.</p>

    <p>Instructors have full access to the system and are allowed to make any changes.
      Graders have largely the same access as students except that they can download
      submitted assignments and modify the entire grade book. Students have no access to
      the user database, no access to the grade book (except for read-only access to their
      own grades), and can modify only their assignment submissions (up to the due date).</p>

